01:26:05.092 --> 01:26:07.119
It is the continual bombardment of, 'Why even try?

01:26:07.119 --> 01:26:23.471
' Like tonight, it is feeling dry—the bombardment of, 'If they experience that, well, I'm inadequate.

01:26:24.622 --> 01:26:38.324
God doesn't like me, he doesn't care about me.

01:26:38.324 --> 01:26:44.675
Well, where is the Lord in my prayer life?

01:26:44.675 --> 01:27:01.502
' God loves you, and feeding on the love of God—feeding on what he said—'God so loved the world that he gave his one and only begotten son, that whosoever believes in him should not perish.

01:27:01.502 --> 01:27:06.220
' I'm the whosoever.

01:27:07.720 --> 01:27:08.020
I am a whosoever.

01:27:10.034 --> 01:27:12.869
I believe that God loves me and I am adequate.

01:27:27.342 --> 01:27:27.546
God died for me.

01:27:27.546 --> 01:27:31.040
Jesus paid the price for me.

01:27:31.040 --> 01:27:33.916
That's it.

01:27:34.874 --> 01:27:38.140
I hit the vein.

01:27:38.140 --> 01:27:40.040
That's it.

01:27:41.267 --> 01:27:50.853
He is saying because there are many who don't feel adequate: 'Well, I don't have a good prayer life.

01:28:17.026 --> 01:28:18.374
He doesn't show me angels.

01:28:46.057 --> 01:28:46.331
He doesn't show me these things, so I'm not adequate tonight.

01:28:46.331 --> 01:28:52.524
I don't feel adequate in my life.

01:28:52.524 --> 01:28:53.880
Where is the anointing?

01:28:53.880 --> 01:28:56.400
Where is the Holy Ghost?

01:28:56.400 --> 01:28:59.863
' You stir yourself up.

01:29:09.239 --> 01:29:09.539
You contend.

01:29:09.539 --> 01:29:12.503
Are you a contender for the glory?

01:29:25.629 --> 01:29:28.869
My father loves me.

01:29:28.869 --> 01:29:30.623
I'm adequate.

01:29:30.623 --> 01:29:31.567
Why?

01:29:43.480 --> 01:29:43.870
Because he gave his life for me.

01:29:43.870 --> 01:29:51.760
If he could, if he would have died only just for me, he would have done it.

01:29:51.760 --> 01:30:03.170
If I was the only one for him to die for, I believe he would have died for me.

01:30:22.343 --> 01:30:22.697
I'm that special to him.

01:30:22.697 --> 01:30:25.520
I'm that special to Jesus.

01:30:25.520 --> 01:30:28.440
You're that special to Jesus.

01:30:28.440 --> 01:30:39.583
If we were the only ones on this earth, Jesus would have died for me.

01:30:59.680 --> 01:31:00.080
One drop of blood set me free.

01:31:00.080 --> 01:31:02.937
Jesus paid the price for me.

01:31:08.354 --> 01:31:08.709
I take authority over the spirit of inadequacy.

01:31:08.709 --> 01:31:13.486
That's so interesting that they're hitting that wall like that and feeling that.

01:31:13.486 --> 01:31:16.391
I know what the Lord is saying right now.

01:31:16.391 --> 01:31:19.120
So many people have it in their mind.

01:31:19.120 --> 01:31:21.387
They listen to the devil all day long.

01:31:33.714 --> 01:31:34.171
It's the bombardment of thoughts of inadequacy filling in the dry places.

01:31:34.171 --> 01:31:35.543
'I'm dry.

01:31:35.543 --> 01:31:36.453
I'm thirsty.

01:31:36.453 --> 01:31:37.360
He's not here.

01:31:37.360 --> 01:31:38.674
He must not care.

01:31:38.674 --> 01:31:38.936
' Where are you?

01:31:38.936 --> 01:31:41.965
Where is this stirring inside of me?

01:31:41.965 --> 01:31:43.108
I'm so dry.

01:31:44.239 --> 01:31:49.119
And that's what the Holy Spirit is talking about tonight.

01:31:49.119 --> 01:31:51.610
Where is the father in the dryness?

01:31:51.610 --> 01:31:53.920
He said, 'I'll never leave you and I'll never forsake you.

01:31:53.920 --> 01:31:57.209
' Find scriptures just like I'm teaching you.

01:31:57.209 --> 01:32:01.130
Find sermons and stir yourself up.

01:32:01.130 --> 01:32:52.470
You've got to bite onto the bone and say, 'I'm a bulldog and I'm not letting go until he blesses me.

01:32:52.480 --> 01:32:55.497
' It's like the wrestling with the angel.

01:32:55.497 --> 01:32:58.671
'I'm not letting go, Jacob.

01:32:58.671 --> 01:33:03.360
I'm not letting go until you bless me.

01:33:03.360 --> 01:33:05.493
' And then the angel finally...

01:33:05.493 --> 01:33:07.813
he walked with a little limp.

01:33:07.813 --> 01:33:12.159
He got what he wanted though.

01:33:12.159 --> 01:33:17.860
How bad do you want a fresh touch to stir in your life?

01:33:17.860 --> 01:33:22.760
How many of you are dealing with this?

01:33:22.760 --> 01:33:23.989
I'm just curious.

01:33:23.989 --> 01:33:27.476
How many of you deal with this feeling of being inadequate?

01:33:27.476 --> 01:33:30.610
How many of you feel that your prayer time is dry?

01:33:30.610 --> 01:33:35.263
Type one in the comment section.

01:33:35.263 --> 01:33:38.539
Do you go through dry seasons in your prayer time?

01:33:38.539 --> 01:33:43.120
Is that what the Lord—because I'm coming across this and this is where the river is at.

01:33:43.120 --> 01:33:53.740
How many of you are coming into your prayer time in the mornings and you just feel dry sometimes like this, or you feel that you're inadequate?

01:33:53.740 --> 01:33:55.371
'Well, I'm not good enough.

01:33:55.371 --> 01:33:58.639
God doesn't love me.

01:33:58.639 --> 01:34:23.980
' Is there anybody out there who feels that he's abandoned you?

01:34:23.980 --> 01:34:26.639
Maybe you don't feel that.

01:34:26.639 --> 01:34:35.480
There are days of just, 'I don't even know why I'm even here praying.

01:34:35.480 --> 01:34:39.859
' I feel it in my spirit.

01:34:41.880 --> 01:34:42.460
You feel so inadequate.

01:34:42.460 --> 01:34:57.339
Maybe it's not, but I just feel inside of my spirit that God is trying to tell you tonight that he loves you and you are adequate.

01:35:23.520 --> 01:35:24.267
I don't know what it comes to tonight, but it's something so much deeper than just Brandon sitting here pushing through.

01:35:24.267 --> 01:35:34.592
It's trying to tell you that even Brandon has to push through.

01:35:34.592 --> 01:35:42.077
And you've got to be a bulldog about this.

01:36:09.040 --> 01:36:09.573
And you cannot get down on yourself and think, 'I don't have what it takes.

01:36:09.573 --> 01:36:18.200
' He wants so bad for you to seek him and you'll find him there in the dryness.

01:36:20.720 --> 01:36:21.020
You are there in the stillness.

01:36:53.360 --> 01:36:53.580
I refuse to feel inadequate anymore.

01:36:53.580 --> 01:36:55.339
Church leadership, don't look at me.

01:36:57.830 --> 01:36:58.400
The upper people don't look at you, but Jesus looks at you.

01:36:58.400 --> 01:37:21.990
Regardless of who looked at you, my father died for me.

01:37:40.560 --> 01:37:40.846
And if I was the only one left on this earth, Christ would have died for me.

01:37:52.400 --> 01:37:52.720
He died for every single one of us.

01:37:52.720 --> 01:37:57.215
But he died for us to live a life full of abundance.

01:37:57.215 --> 01:38:12.130
But even in the valley of dryness, even in the valley of feeling inadequate, he made me.

01:38:12.130 --> 01:38:15.194
Christ in me.

01:38:15.194 --> 01:38:18.990
Christ in me, the hope of glory.

01:38:18.990 --> 01:38:25.034
Christ in me tonight.

01:38:25.034 --> 01:38:31.520
As he is, so am I in this world.

01:38:31.520 --> 01:38:40.990
I'm moved by that more than I am by the way I feel.

01:38:40.990 --> 01:39:50.790
Faith is not something that you are going to feel.

01:39:50.800 --> 01:39:56.200
Faith calls those things that be not as though they were.

01:39:56.200 --> 01:40:04.320
Faith is the substance of things hoped for and evidence of things not seen.

01:40:04.320 --> 01:40:06.871
It's not something you've seen.

01:40:08.480 --> 01:40:10.239
You believe it even when you don't see it.

01:40:10.239 --> 01:40:52.194
Abraham staggered not at the promise of God through unbelief, but was strong in faith, giving glory to God, fully persuaded that what he had promised, he was able also to perform.

01:40:52.194 --> 01:40:55.760
He was fully persuaded in his dryness.

01:40:55.760 --> 01:41:04.080
It doesn't make sense, and in the deadness of Sarah's womb, he was fully persuaded.

01:41:04.080 --> 01:42:02.780
Even when Sarah couldn't conceive and her ovaries were like raisins—she's like, 'I don't have it.

01:42:02.780 --> 01:42:06.080
I don't got what it takes.

01:42:06.080 --> 01:42:07.999
I'm inadequate.

01:42:07.999 --> 01:42:42.060
' But God said, 'Sarah, you're going to have a baby.

01:42:42.060 --> 01:42:48.640
' And in her inadequacy, he spoke to the dryness in her womb and he said, 'Life be.

01:42:48.640 --> 01:43:15.616
' And he was not moved by what he saw.

01:43:15.616 --> 01:43:18.347
He was not moved by it.

01:43:18.347 --> 01:43:23.280
He staggered not at the promise of God.

01:43:23.280 --> 01:43:30.379
'Abraham, you're going to be a father of many nations.

01:43:30.379 --> 01:43:33.208
Abraham, you're going to walk in the blessing.

01:43:33.208 --> 01:43:37.407
Abraham, you're going to be a father one day.

01:43:37.407 --> 01:43:41.259
' And he's like, 'I'm old.

01:43:44.569 --> 01:43:44.818
I don't have...

01:43:44.818 --> 01:43:46.062
' He trusts God.

01:43:54.144 --> 01:43:54.592
It's the truth.

01:43:54.592 --> 01:44:02.320
He staggered not at the promise of God through unbelief, but was strong in faith, giving glory to God.

01:44:02.320 --> 01:44:12.444
You can't be moved by what you see, even in the deadness of Sarah's womb, even the deadness of your spiritual walk.

01:44:12.444 --> 01:44:14.800
Somebody said, 'It's the truth, Ruth.

01:44:14.800 --> 01:44:16.000
' I like that.

01:44:16.000 --> 01:44:18.347
I'm going to start using that.

01:44:18.347 --> 01:44:21.954
He wasn't moved by what he sees.

01:44:21.954 --> 01:44:24.880
He was staggered not at the promise of God.

01:44:24.880 --> 01:44:38.880
He knew he was inadequate at that time in his own ability to receive, but God spoke to him and said, 'Either you're going to walk this way or you're not.

01:44:38.880 --> 01:44:42.649
Either you're a believing believer, Abraham, or you're not.

01:44:42.649 --> 01:44:48.080
' And Abraham grabbed a hold of the promise and said, 'I'm not moved by what I see.

01:44:50.103 --> 01:44:50.320
I'm not moved by what I feel.

01:45:05.560 --> 01:45:05.920
I'm old.

01:45:05.920 --> 01:45:06.880
She's old.

01:45:06.880 --> 01:45:11.580
' That's the same way you do with your spiritual walk.

01:45:21.164 --> 01:45:21.413
I don't feel adequate.

01:45:27.200 --> 01:45:27.520
God called me; He chose me for such a time as this.

01:45:34.133 --> 01:45:35.199
He let me be born in this time frame, and I know that He didn't make a mistake.

01:45:35.199 --> 01:45:36.400
God doesn't make mistakes.

01:45:43.270 --> 01:45:45.919
They say, "Well, my mama didn't want me.

01:45:47.999 --> 01:45:48.199
She was going to have an abortion.

01:45:48.199 --> 01:45:51.736
She didn't even want me; I was an unwanted child.

01:45:51.736 --> 01:45:53.216
" God doesn't make mistakes.

01:45:53.216 --> 01:45:54.750
You're not a mistake.

01:45:54.750 --> 01:45:55.800
You're here.

01:45:55.800 --> 01:45:59.673
Your mama had you, and you're a blessing to this earth.

01:45:59.673 --> 01:46:05.340
God has called you and chose you for such a time as this.

01:46:05.340 --> 01:46:09.590
Regardless of whether she said, "Well, I heard she didn't want me.

01:46:09.590 --> 01:46:13.611
" Well, my dad didn't want another daughter; he wanted a son.

01:46:31.140 --> 01:46:31.450
And I feel inadequate, and I should have been here.

01:46:31.450 --> 01:46:41.488
You know, my father didn't want me; he wanted a boy instead of a girl, or he wanted a girl instead of a boy.

01:46:41.488 --> 01:46:44.952
But God chose you, and you are who you are.

01:46:50.039 --> 01:46:50.459
And you're fearfully and wonderfully made.

01:46:50.459 --> 01:46:52.560
There are no mistakes.

01:46:52.560 --> 01:46:55.493
There are no mistakes.

01:46:55.493 --> 01:47:00.709
And I'm telling you all, it's time we get a hold of the promises of God.

01:47:00.709 --> 01:47:07.234
He says, "I have a plan for you, I love you, and I died for you individually.

01:47:07.234 --> 01:47:12.800
" And Abraham staggered not at the promise of God, and we need to stagger not at the promise of God.

01:47:12.800 --> 01:47:16.379
What did He promise you in your heart?

01:47:16.819 --> 01:47:17.920
The desires of your heart.

01:47:17.920 --> 01:47:21.246
What's in your heart and your biggest desires?

01:47:34.550 --> 01:47:34.760
"I want a relationship with my father.

01:47:34.760 --> 01:47:45.840
" If you're feeling inadequate, a good thing would be to look at the scriptures He said about you and claim them because your job is just to receive it.

01:47:45.840 --> 01:47:50.971
Receive everything He said for you and say it over yourself.

01:47:52.297 --> 01:47:55.600
You said that You knit me together in my mother's womb.

01:47:59.223 --> 01:48:00.526
You said that I am called this.

01:48:08.840 --> 01:48:09.040
You call me blessed.

01:48:09.040 --> 01:48:10.240
You call me a blessing.

01:48:10.240 --> 01:48:13.813
Deuteronomy 28, what I read earlier—You call me these things.

01:48:13.813 --> 01:48:21.119
And I am adequate because You've called me to be adequate even in this.

01:48:32.260 --> 01:48:32.750
And I don't know why I got off on the topic of adequacy, but that's the word the Lord gave me a second ago.

01:48:42.175 --> 01:48:42.407
And He said a lot of them feel that they're going through dry seasons in their prayer life, their marriage, or their job.

01:48:42.407 --> 01:48:47.510
They're going through dry seasons in a lot of areas of their life right now.

01:48:47.510 --> 01:48:53.560
And in 2025, there's a lot of you who are weary in well-doing, ready to let go of the rope.

01:49:01.520 --> 01:49:01.813
"I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me.

01:49:01.813 --> 01:49:03.300
" Call your life a success.

01:49:03.300 --> 01:49:06.347
I heard this right then: get an inner image of it.

01:49:06.347 --> 01:49:08.427
See yourself as God sees you.

01:49:22.128 --> 01:49:22.392
You have to have that picture.

01:49:26.328 --> 01:49:26.560
I get the vision inside of me of what He said I could be.

01:49:26.560 --> 01:49:27.304
See it.

01:49:27.304 --> 01:49:28.296
See yourself successful.

01:49:36.754 --> 01:49:43.759
You know, maybe if you're a heavy-set guy like me, you look at some buff dude who has huge muscles and say, "That's a vision.

01:49:45.499 --> 01:49:51.227
I can see myself being that.

01:49:51.227 --> 01:49:59.200
I'm not going to be the heavy guy that's always the fat kid on the playground that nobody wants to pick, the last pick in sports.

01:49:59.200 --> 01:50:04.506
" You have that image of saying, "That's who I am spiritually.

01:50:04.506 --> 01:50:09.080
I'm going to be the muscle man spiritually.

01:50:09.080 --> 01:50:12.010
I'm going to be the muscle man physically.

01:50:12.010 --> 01:50:14.984
I'm going to take care of my temple.

01:50:20.080 --> 01:50:20.944
" But if you don't see it, you're not going to have an inner image of it to achieve it.

01:50:20.944 --> 01:50:22.779
That's why I drive around rich neighborhoods.

01:50:22.779 --> 01:50:26.301
People with multi-million dollar houses—they might have a $10 million house.

01:50:26.444 --> 01:50:27.980
I look at them and just park outside.

01:50:27.980 --> 01:50:29.808
They probably think, "That guy's stalking me.

01:50:35.390 --> 01:50:35.980
" But no, I'm trying to get an image of it.

01:50:35.980 --> 01:50:44.760
If they are of the world and I'm God's kid, how much more could I have that than them?

01:50:44.760 --> 01:50:49.760
They are heathens; they don't know Him, yet they have my harvest and my blessing.

01:50:51.740 --> 01:50:54.453
And the wealth of the sinner is laid up for the righteous.

01:50:59.472 --> 01:51:01.487
So I drive around getting that image inside of me instead of always thinking poor.

01:51:01.487 --> 01:51:04.666
If you're always around poverty, you can't see blessing.

01:51:04.666 --> 01:51:07.977
If you're always thinking poor, it's going to stay in you.

01:51:07.977 --> 01:51:15.120
You've got to change the image in your mind from scripture to seeing blessing, thinking blessing.

01:51:15.120 --> 01:51:16.034
Change your thinking.

01:51:16.034 --> 01:51:25.440
If you're always thinking obese—the Lord always told me, "Brandon, as a man thinketh in his heart, so is he.

01:51:25.440 --> 01:51:26.399
" That's scripture.

01:51:26.399 --> 01:51:31.424
If I see myself as spiritually inadequate—as a man thinketh in his heart, so is he.

01:51:31.424 --> 01:51:34.258
Same with poverty, same with eating or whatever.

01:51:34.258 --> 01:51:36.630
If I always see myself as obese, I'll always have it.

01:51:36.630 --> 01:51:39.620
As a man thinketh in his heart, so is he.

01:51:53.430 --> 01:51:53.620
Out of the abundance of the heart, your mouth speaks.

01:51:53.620 --> 01:51:54.587
I am fit.

01:51:54.587 --> 01:51:55.760
I am healthy.

01:51:55.760 --> 01:51:59.920
I will live long and finish strong.

01:51:59.920 --> 01:52:03.760
I will not have these weight issues anymore.

01:52:03.760 --> 01:52:11.120
I deal with obesity and an eating disorder of thinking—eating for comfort instead of eating for fuel.

01:52:11.120 --> 01:52:13.591
Well, I'm going to change that.

01:52:13.591 --> 01:52:30.800
You know, but if you keep thinking that—for people who don't deal with that, you don't know until you have an eating disorder and you go, "Man, this is something where I'm calling those things that are not as though they were.

01:52:45.474 --> 01:52:45.840
" I don't want to deal with this.

01:52:47.328 --> 01:52:48.507
I break this generational curse off of my life.

01:52:58.800 --> 01:52:59.000
My mom was fat, her mom was fat, and her dad was fat.

01:52:59.000 --> 01:53:00.731
No, I don't have that.

01:53:00.731 --> 01:53:03.931
My kids won't deal with that.

01:53:12.213 --> 01:53:12.560
It stops with me.

01:53:12.560 --> 01:53:14.388
Poverty stops with me.

01:53:14.388 --> 01:53:18.343
Well, my mom and dad were poor, and their mom and dad were poor.

01:53:18.343 --> 01:53:19.280
Everybody was poor.

01:53:22.976 --> 01:53:23.224
You know, my great-granny, who is 106 years old, dealt with poverty.

01:53:23.224 --> 01:53:24.960
No, poverty stops with me.

01:53:24.960 --> 01:53:29.821
You've got to get that inside of you.

01:53:31.199 --> 01:53:32.199
I am going to walk with the King.

01:53:32.199 --> 01:53:37.404
So, going back to it, I will have a spiritual walk where I feel adequate.

01:53:37.404 --> 01:53:38.655
God's called me.

01:53:38.655 --> 01:53:43.820
And dryness is only for a season; I'm not going to be dry.

01:53:43.820 --> 01:53:45.160
Tomorrow's another day.

01:53:45.160 --> 01:53:47.246
You've got to keep going.

01:53:47.246 --> 01:53:49.326
Does that help you all?

01:54:03.992 --> 01:54:04.224
I mean, this is just what's coming out of my spirit now.

01:54:10.179 --> 01:54:10.359
And I'm thankful for it because I didn't know where to go, and now all of a sudden, this is falling.

01:54:10.359 --> 01:54:13.543
So I'm like, "Okay, Holy Ghost, thank you for helping me.

01:54:13.543 --> 01:54:15.406
" It's just real, y'all.

01:54:17.189 --> 01:54:20.366
And I'm telling y'all, this is what you do.

01:54:26.660 --> 01:54:27.010
The Lord said, "Lead by example" earlier, and I was like, "Lead by example?

01:54:27.010 --> 01:54:29.209
Well, I don't know where I'm going.

01:54:37.920 --> 01:54:39.520
What do you want me to do?

01:54:39.520 --> 01:54:40.020
" Okay.

01:54:40.020 --> 01:54:40.520
Hallelujah.

01:54:45.272 --> 01:54:45.488
So, Father, we just keep pouring it out.

01:54:45.488 --> 01:54:47.570
I sure love you, Braden.

01:54:47.570 --> 01:54:52.016
Braden knows; he gets it because he was raised by us.

01:54:52.016 --> 01:54:55.097
But Father, we just thank You, Lord.

01:54:55.097 --> 01:54:58.480
We just thank You, Father, for Your hand on us.

01:54:58.480 --> 01:55:04.259
Now, Father, after I got through that, is there anything You want to show us?

01:55:04.259 --> 01:55:07.849
Lord, I just felt like that was something.

01:55:07.849 --> 01:55:14.409
So, whenever I got to that, Lord, I really felt like it was a lot.

01:55:14.409 --> 01:55:16.880
It was just what You wanted to say tonight about that.

01:55:16.880 --> 01:55:21.199
But Lord, I still feel an urgency to pray for things.

01:55:21.199 --> 01:55:29.900
Is there anything coming for the nations tonight that You want me to relay to the people?

01:55:38.937 --> 01:55:39.349
I'm telling you, I'm hitting that wall.

01:55:39.349 --> 01:55:42.927
He spoke about feeling inadequate.

01:55:42.927 --> 01:55:52.159
It's all about the people feeling that they don't have what it takes to finish the race.

01:55:52.159 --> 01:55:59.733
They are adequate, but there's such a wound in people—a deep sorrow of feeling the inadequacy.

01:56:02.920 --> 01:56:03.140
"I don't have what it takes.

01:56:03.140 --> 01:56:05.460
" I hear them in their thoughts.

01:56:05.460 --> 01:56:08.091
"I don't have what it takes.

01:56:08.091 --> 01:56:09.920
Where's God for me?

01:56:09.920 --> 01:56:11.180
Where is God for me?

01:56:11.180 --> 01:56:14.140
" He says, "Where is God for me?

01:56:23.070 --> 01:56:23.380
I feel so abandoned.

01:56:27.280 --> 01:56:27.480
I feel so alone.

01:56:27.480 --> 01:56:31.160
" It's very interesting coming up to that wall.

01:56:37.325 --> 01:56:37.714
You feel it.

01:56:50.471 --> 01:56:50.756
You can feel it.

01:56:51.240 --> 01:56:51.840
You can hear them.

01:56:51.840 --> 01:56:57.327
There's so many people saying that inside of their hearts: "Where is God for me?

01:56:57.327 --> 01:56:58.902
I feel so inadequate.

01:57:04.620 --> 01:57:04.880
My prayer language isn't enough.

01:57:05.111 --> 01:57:06.960
I don't pray in tongues well enough.

01:57:06.960 --> 01:57:08.960
I don't hear God well enough.

01:57:12.080 --> 01:57:12.311
" I don't pray in tongues well enough.

01:57:12.773 --> 01:57:16.160
I feel so inadequate for where I want to be.

01:57:16.160 --> 01:57:18.674
How come I don't hear God?

01:57:18.674 --> 01:57:21.883
They say, 'I don't feel like I hear God.

01:57:21.883 --> 01:57:26.639
How do I know if it is God when he is talking to me?

01:57:26.639 --> 01:57:28.600
' I feel so alone.

01:57:28.600 --> 01:57:29.771
Don't you see?

01:57:29.771 --> 01:57:33.429
How do I know when it's God talking to me?

01:57:39.450 --> 01:57:39.760
I feel so inadequate tonight.

01:57:41.636 --> 01:57:41.991
I feel so alone.

01:57:41.991 --> 01:57:43.413
Nobody understands me.

01:57:43.413 --> 01:57:45.879
These are the things I'm hearing.

01:57:45.879 --> 01:57:50.524
Does he really truly care about me?

01:57:50.524 --> 01:57:52.360
I'm at the end of my rope.

01:57:52.360 --> 01:57:53.031
Don't you see?

01:58:01.147 --> 01:58:01.333
Why have you abandoned me?

01:58:01.333 --> 01:58:03.800
God probably cares, but he doesn't care about me.

01:58:03.800 --> 01:58:07.383
See how the enemy would try to build all this around you?

01:58:07.383 --> 01:58:09.040
There's so much of that I'm hearing.

01:58:15.627 --> 01:58:15.840
And those are lies from the devil.

01:58:15.840 --> 01:58:22.959
He feeds those lies because it goes strictly against his word.

01:58:35.862 --> 01:58:36.057
But because you are moved by what you see, you are allowing your flesh to dominate you and your thoughts.

01:58:45.733 --> 01:58:45.1000
It's why I keep telling you: I'm not moved by what I see.

01:58:45.1000 --> 01:58:49.679
I'm not moved by what I feel.

01:58:49.679 --> 01:58:52.666
I'm moved by what the Word of God says.

01:58:52.666 --> 01:58:54.000
My Father loves me.

01:58:54.000 --> 01:59:02.936
First John 4:7-8 says: 'Beloved, let us love one another, for love is of God; and everyone that loveth is born of God and knoweth God.

01:59:08.400 --> 01:59:08.720
He that loveth not knoweth not God, for God is love.

01:59:08.720 --> 01:59:12.514
' Beloved, let us love one another.

01:59:12.514 --> 01:59:14.400
That's where it's at.

01:59:14.400 --> 01:59:25.154
But you've got to know inside of you that all those things that you're hearing, and what I'm hearing you saying...

01:59:37.520 --> 01:59:37.920
it's interesting.

01:59:48.755 --> 01:59:48.960
In the vision that I just had, I saw what looked like a whirlwind.

01:59:48.960 --> 01:59:50.701
It was a big drain.

01:59:54.180 --> 01:59:54.520
And each person was like a YouTube screen.

02:00:04.879 --> 02:00:05.439
You know how you can scan the thumbnails and see all the different pictures?

02:00:05.439 --> 02:00:10.204
There were literally thousands of your faces going in a whirlwind.

02:00:10.461 --> 02:00:18.239
It was a drain before me, and each one had a person inside, and everybody was saying something all at once.

02:00:25.863 --> 02:00:30.415
And as it's moving in this drain, as I'm praying, I hear you saying this from your heart—the things that I was repeating just then.

02:00:43.280 --> 02:00:43.451
I was hearing it, and as that would swing by, I could hear you getting louder as it hit my ear.

02:00:49.340 --> 02:00:53.261
It moved away, and I could hear you for a split second moving by me, and you were going down the drain.

02:00:53.261 --> 02:00:57.040
Your thoughts are going down the drain.

02:00:57.040 --> 02:00:57.760
It's trash.

02:00:59.129 --> 02:00:59.298
Don't think it.

02:00:59.298 --> 02:01:02.640
What you meditate on the most is what you'll become.

02:01:02.640 --> 02:01:05.731
You've got to change your thought pattern.

02:01:06.022 --> 02:01:11.599
I saw it turning before me, and as I was turning, each one of you was moving before me.

02:01:12.159 --> 02:01:13.560
I could hear your thoughts.

02:01:18.500 --> 02:01:18.760
I could hear what you were saying inside of your heart.

02:01:18.760 --> 02:01:23.218
All those things that I was repeating just a second ago.

02:01:23.218 --> 02:01:28.263
There's this lady—somebody who lives in an apartment with steps going up.

02:01:29.051 --> 02:01:32.350
You live in an apartment complex, and you're walking up these steps.

02:01:32.350 --> 02:01:34.720
There is gray siding on your building.

02:01:34.720 --> 02:01:38.880
You live on the second floor, and you're crying out for more.

02:01:44.080 --> 02:01:44.320
I see where you live as this thing's moving around.

02:01:55.200 --> 02:01:55.360
You walked up the steps, and you live in the door on the right-hand side.

02:01:58.1000 --> 02:01:59.280
I can see your steps.

02:01:59.280 --> 02:02:01.040
I can see where you are.

02:02:03.759 --> 02:02:04.379
You live right where the steps end, in that door right there.

02:02:04.379 --> 02:02:05.920
There's a window right here.

02:02:05.920 --> 02:02:08.239
I see where you're living.

02:02:08.239 --> 02:02:12.160
There looked like some snow at the bottom of your steps in the yard.

02:02:12.160 --> 02:02:17.839
Oh Lord, you're giving the Lord an ultimatum: 'Either you fix this in me, or I'm going to do something to myself.

02:02:17.839 --> 02:02:20.320
' That's what you say.

02:02:20.320 --> 02:02:23.261
'I'm not going to live like this anymore.

02:02:23.261 --> 02:02:28.525
I'm giving you until this time frame to fix this, or I'm going to do this.

02:02:28.525 --> 02:02:33.419
' You're crying out to the Father so much that your heart is grieving.

02:02:44.666 --> 02:02:45.053
You're so empty.

02:02:45.053 --> 02:02:46.346
You're single.

02:02:52.773 --> 02:02:53.040
You don't have a husband or even a boyfriend.

02:03:07.341 --> 02:03:07.653
You say, 'I'm tired of being alone.

02:03:07.653 --> 02:03:10.891
No one to even call on the phone.

02:03:10.891 --> 02:03:12.880
' Oh, I see it.

02:03:12.880 --> 02:03:20.409
Ma'am, you're so hurt, but Jesus loves you so much—so much that he would show me this right now.

02:03:30.144 --> 02:03:30.400
He has a plan for your life.

02:03:30.400 --> 02:03:35.230
'Come unto me, all ye that are heavy laden, and I will give you rest.

02:03:35.230 --> 02:03:44.540
' As you're climbing those steps at night by yourself and you go into that empty room and live in that cold apartment, watching TV by yourself...

02:03:47.086 --> 02:03:49.440
you watch us on this YouTube, and Jesus sees you right where you are.

02:03:57.659 --> 02:03:57.840
I don't know what that white is—if it's not snow, it's dead grass for sure.

02:03:57.840 --> 02:04:00.213
He wants to become so real to you.

02:04:01.497 --> 02:04:17.191
There's so many of you—this probably fits a category, not maybe of the apartment complex, but you're saying the exact same thing she's saying: 'I'm so alone.

02:04:25.689 --> 02:04:25.884
I have nobody.

02:04:25.884 --> 02:04:30.168
' During this holiday season, it's even harder on you.

02:04:30.168 --> 02:04:32.355
You think, 'Does God care?

02:04:32.355 --> 02:04:35.181
' But I'm telling you, God cares.

02:04:35.181 --> 02:04:37.164
He cares about you being alone.

02:04:37.164 --> 02:04:42.560
He cares about you feeling like you have nobody to call on the phone.

02:04:42.560 --> 02:04:43.759
Jesus cares about you.

02:04:43.759 --> 02:04:52.008
Instead of saying, 'If this doesn't change, I'm ending it all,' say, 'This is the beginning of my new start.

02:04:52.008 --> 02:04:56.130
As of tonight, this is the beginning of my new start.

02:04:56.130 --> 02:04:58.388
' I have something to live for.

02:04:58.388 --> 02:05:02.239
God has so much more in store.

02:05:02.239 --> 02:05:03.079
That's beautiful.

02:05:05.006 --> 02:05:05.269
The sorrow is no longer.

02:05:05.269 --> 02:05:10.551
Thank you, Lord, for all that you have in store—that in 2026 we will soar.

02:05:10.551 --> 02:05:13.422
Father, I thank you.

02:05:22.840 --> 02:05:23.049
The greater the days ahead.

02:05:39.280 --> 02:05:39.600
The more you have for us.

02:05:39.600 --> 02:05:42.000
Oh, Father, I thank you, Lord.

02:05:42.000 --> 02:05:42.960
Stir inside yourself.

02:05:42.960 --> 02:05:46.160
We call it a move in your spirit man.

02:05:46.160 --> 02:05:50.551
We call it stirred in the name of Jesus.

02:05:50.551 --> 02:05:54.755
Oh, Father, we thank you, Lord, for fresh fire of the Holy Ghost.

02:06:07.031 --> 02:06:07.209
We thank you for the Holy Spirit, Lord, that you move inside of these individuals tonight.

02:06:11.480 --> 02:06:11.680
You stir inside of them.

02:06:11.680 --> 02:06:14.823
Do you have anything, hun?

02:06:20.503 --> 02:06:20.834
I find that it's harder when my Word level's low.

02:06:20.834 --> 02:06:23.280
It's harder when I get busy.

02:06:23.280 --> 02:06:32.583
That feeling of inadequacy has a lot to do with how I was raised, because I was abused as a child and it tried to make me feel inadequate.

02:06:32.583 --> 02:06:36.320
But the Lord has brought me so far from where I was.

02:06:36.992 --> 02:06:42.130
I feel like as I get in the word more, it's helped me a lot.

02:06:42.130 --> 02:06:44.746
It's just staying—it's not allowing the thoughts.

02:06:44.746 --> 02:06:46.987
It's just fighting the good fight of faith.

02:06:46.987 --> 02:06:51.610
On days whenever it's like that, I put Kathryn Kuhlman on or I listen to it, and it helps.

02:07:02.800 --> 02:07:03.040
It's like you're getting punched, and when you're getting punched, you don't succumb to it.

02:07:03.040 --> 02:07:04.240
You have to fight.

02:07:14.079 --> 02:07:14.309
You get even with what you're just saying right then about being abused.

02:07:14.309 --> 02:07:15.920
People don't know your story.

02:07:15.920 --> 02:07:23.400
A lot of people don't know your childhood and being raised—you were sometimes in a car for how many months without food?

02:07:25.499 --> 02:07:26.079
Yeah.

02:07:26.079 --> 02:07:28.480
Well, okay, so you want me to tell the story?

02:07:28.480 --> 02:07:31.080
You can say some of it.

02:07:31.080 --> 02:07:32.897
A lot of people need to hear it.

02:07:33.976 --> 02:07:34.274
You don't ever talk.

02:07:34.274 --> 02:07:36.148
So, that's what I'm saying.

02:07:36.148 --> 02:07:41.840
There's a lot of people who don't know your story about you and how you were raised.

02:07:41.840 --> 02:07:45.462
Your dad was a preacher.

02:07:45.462 --> 02:07:46.148
Yes.

02:07:51.032 --> 02:07:51.184
I was raised Baptist.

02:07:51.184 --> 02:07:51.792
No, not Baptist.

02:07:51.792 --> 02:07:53.013
Sorry, he was not Baptist.

02:07:53.013 --> 02:07:54.035
I'm Assemblies of God.

02:07:54.035 --> 02:07:59.679
He was an Assemblies of God pastor; that's a lot different.

02:07:59.679 --> 02:08:02.827
Yeah, we were too Pentecostal for that.

02:08:03.303 --> 02:08:11.160
It's late, but that is what he—I'm not laughing at you.

02:08:11.790 --> 02:08:14.159
I just, when you say Baptist, I was like...

02:08:18.649 --> 02:08:19.119
I messed it up.

02:08:19.119 --> 02:08:22.503
You're AG, Assemblies of God.

02:08:22.503 --> 02:08:24.560
Yes, Assemblies of God pastor.

02:08:24.560 --> 02:08:32.274
Well, they got a divorce when I was 11, but he had been abused a lot as a kid, too.

02:08:32.274 --> 02:08:33.573
So, he brought that.

02:08:33.573 --> 02:08:38.407
It just came in because they wanted a boy and they had me.

02:08:38.407 --> 02:08:44.036
My mom told me that she wished that I was a boy because that was what they wanted.

02:08:44.036 --> 02:08:46.259
So, I knew that from a small child.

02:08:47.565 --> 02:08:48.833
And then he was abusive.

02:08:48.833 --> 02:08:54.880
My dad was abusive to me.

02:08:54.880 --> 02:09:00.264
Whenever I was in church, I got pinched if I moved.

02:09:00.264 --> 02:09:10.605
If I said the wrong thing, I got spankings all the time, more than any of my other siblings.

02:09:25.760 --> 02:09:26.359
And just a lot of hard stuff like I don't really like talking about, but we lived in a car for a long time because my dad would just disappear.

02:09:26.359 --> 02:09:40.194
He got let go from his pastoral job at the Assemblies of God, and it really derailed him a lot, so it kind of affected how he acted even more.

02:09:40.194 --> 02:09:42.720
He didn't take any other job.

02:09:42.720 --> 02:09:47.180
So, he was at home a lot with me and my mom was gone a lot.

02:09:51.030 --> 02:09:52.936
I was abused probably the most out of my siblings, physically and verbally, but never sexually.

02:09:52.936 --> 02:09:55.050
Thank the Lord for that.

02:10:04.480 --> 02:10:04.809
I think He was definitely praying for me.

02:10:04.809 --> 02:10:11.733
So, definitely keep praying for your spouse—the one that you're going to meet, that God has for you.

02:10:11.733 --> 02:10:22.383
Pray for them because you don't realize that they might really need that, because I feel like that really helped me.

02:10:36.675 --> 02:10:37.700
The Lord kept me through all of that.

02:10:46.719 --> 02:10:47.502
We would have so many good miracles in the middle of that.

02:10:47.697 --> 02:10:54.960
As kids, we were homeschooled a lot, but my dad took us away from friends and family, so we weren't around anybody.

02:10:54.960 --> 02:11:15.611
When we went to places, I would get in trouble for saying the wrong thing or doing the wrong thing because I was a pastor's kid, so I would get in trouble behind the scenes more than anything.

02:11:18.040 --> 02:11:21.040
It affected the way I acted, the way I talked, it affected everything.

02:11:21.040 --> 02:11:34.760
When you're a child and you're in that delicate growing stage and you are dealing with so much of that, I didn't realize how much it affected me.

02:11:40.309 --> 02:11:40.686
But that was just a crucible.

02:11:42.200 --> 02:11:44.576
I think that's what a lot of you probably have dealt with.

02:11:48.079 --> 02:11:48.879
I mean, I know I'm not the only one.

02:11:48.879 --> 02:11:54.140
There's a lot of people who have dealt with childhood abuse, whether it's verbally, physically, or sexually.

02:11:55.511 --> 02:11:55.733
I know I'm not alone.

02:11:56.178 --> 02:11:58.880
I know there's people that have had it way worse than me.

02:11:58.880 --> 02:12:02.872
We lived in a car.

02:12:02.872 --> 02:12:04.819
We ate ketchup packets for a while, and a lot of different things.

02:12:10.589 --> 02:12:10.939
My dad would disappear.

02:12:10.939 --> 02:12:19.109
We bathed in the truck stop with a sink.

02:12:35.199 --> 02:12:35.519
We went to the truck stop and we would take baths in the sink.

02:12:35.519 --> 02:12:47.104
Sometimes we would go to a church and my dad would just travel there, and he would get in with the people and the pastors, and they would like him.

02:12:47.104 --> 02:12:51.579
Then he would get the keys or something—he wouldn't tell them—but we lived in the church.

02:13:03.509 --> 02:13:04.057
We lived in the back of the church.

02:13:08.257 --> 02:13:18.533
I remember they would all leave and he was pretending to lock up, and then we hid our stuff under a table at the church in the back.

02:13:33.120 --> 02:13:33.460
We would pull the stuff out, like blankets and stuff, and we slept there.

02:13:33.460 --> 02:13:38.753
For years it was like that, and then he would just disappear.

02:13:44.520 --> 02:13:47.840
I remember so many birthdays where he wasn't there, and my mom was trying to work a lot, so she was really just absent a lot.

02:13:49.720 --> 02:13:57.085
I kind of had times when I had to fend for myself and just a lot of traumatizing little things like that through my whole entire childhood.

02:13:57.085 --> 02:14:04.960
It really affected me in ways that I still feel like the Lord's bringing me out of.

02:14:04.960 --> 02:14:13.919
All that to say, I don't like to focus on all that, but just because y'all haven't heard that story—that's just the CliffsNotes.

02:14:13.919 --> 02:14:19.448
That's the CliffsNotes, but a lot of the stuff that she deals with is from rejection.

02:14:19.448 --> 02:14:22.719
Rejection is—and you're still getting through it.

02:14:22.719 --> 02:14:23.999
Yes.

02:14:23.999 --> 02:14:25.290
It's in layers.

02:14:25.290 --> 02:14:28.140
It feels like an onion.

02:14:37.192 --> 02:14:37.456
I will go, 'I forgive him, I forgive him.

02:14:37.456 --> 02:14:42.693
' None of my siblings talk to my dad, but I will talk to him.

02:14:51.902 --> 02:14:53.040
I talked to him on the phone, but then he'll just change his phone number and I can't get a hold of him still.

02:14:53.040 --> 02:15:03.645
But I forgave him, and that took so much work with the Lord, with the Holy Spirit, for me to even be able to get there.

02:15:03.645 --> 02:15:05.199
But it's layers.

02:15:05.199 --> 02:15:07.840
It's not something that happens overnight.

02:15:08.260 --> 02:15:11.656
You have to be in partnership with the Holy Spirit on a day-to-day basis.

02:15:11.656 --> 02:15:39.520
I rely so much on him and he'll say—just taking a lot of time to listen and not talk so much because I know a lot of times in the past, whenever you feel like you're just pouring your guts out to God and you're just talking and talking and talking, it feels like—I relied so much as a kid on making good grades because that's how I got my parents' attention, so it taught me to be more sense-ruled.

02:15:39.520 --> 02:15:57.040
Thinking using intelligence instead of—because I saw in the spirit as a kid and my dad one time freaked out on me because I said I was talking to an angel, and he was like, 'Well, what was it saying?

02:15:57.040 --> 02:16:00.980
Don't ever do that again.

02:16:00.980 --> 02:16:07.005
' So it made me question a lot of things.

02:16:07.005 --> 02:16:19.119
All of those things combined, and having a bad relationship with my dad, has really affected how I have had to work at having a relationship with God.

02:16:21.680 --> 02:16:30.879
I know there's a lot of people out here that have had bad relationships with parents, or an absent dad, orphans and all of that.

02:16:30.879 --> 02:16:41.359
When you don't have a good father, or one that's there or one that you're able to talk to, it does affect your relationship with God.

02:16:41.359 --> 02:17:08.299
It affects how you can come to him because when your earthly father is gone or he's never there, or he says, 'I'll come to your birthday,' but then he never comes, you have that expectation, especially when you're a child, that it affects you and how you view your relationship with God.

02:17:09.079 --> 02:17:14.628
And then after Megan got diagnosed and all of that, it really just takes away that trust.

02:17:14.628 --> 02:17:19.510
It tries to affect that trust that you've trusted him.

02:17:29.930 --> 02:17:31.165
Lord, I trust you.

02:17:40.640 --> 02:17:51.226
And so I had to just come to the point where I was like, 'God, I don't feel like I can completely trust you.

02:18:10.444 --> 02:18:10.746
I want to; I need you to help me to get there.

02:18:10.746 --> 02:18:23.120
' And so doing that and just pouring my guts out to him every day, he'll say, 'Diana, do this' in these little things.

02:18:23.120 --> 02:18:26.999
But a lot of times when you're sin-ruled, you think, 'I have to...

02:18:26.999 --> 02:18:29.793
if it doesn't happen this way...

02:18:29.793 --> 02:18:37.280
' You feel like, 'I have to do this to make God accept me' because that's the way my parents were.

02:18:37.280 --> 02:18:47.896
With my earthly parents, I had to make good grades for them to accept me.

02:18:55.639 --> 02:18:56.039
So you feel like you have to do this much prayer, this much time, this much work to get there.

02:18:57.794 --> 02:19:00.636
And then if I do this, then he looks at me.

02:19:00.636 --> 02:19:20.891
If I fast for five hours a day, or if I fast for a month—however long it is—if I read an X amount of time to the point where it becomes where I think a lot of believers get to that point where you feel like you have to earn God's favor, right?

02:19:21.970 --> 02:19:22.890
You have to earn God's anointing.

02:19:29.298 --> 02:19:29.662
You have to earn God's hand on your life.

02:19:29.662 --> 02:19:32.960
But it's by grace.

02:19:35.550 --> 02:19:40.680
And that's why I try to tell her all the time: you don't have to do anything for God to love you.

02:19:40.680 --> 02:19:42.160
He already loves you.

02:19:42.160 --> 02:19:46.152
He already died for you.

02:19:46.448 --> 02:19:53.448
